				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\rm{Y}}}_{{\rm{ijk}}}={\rm{\mu }}+{{\rm{G}}}_{{\rm{i}}}+{{\rm{E}}}_{{\rm{j}}}+{{\rm{GE}}}_{{\rm{ij}}}+{{\rm{e}}}_{{\rm{ijk}}},$$\end{document}Yijk=μ+Gi+Ej+GEij+eijk,where Yijk = the phenotypic mean of the cross of variety i and organ j in the kth block; μ = population mean; Gi = the variety effect; Ej = the organ effect; GEij = the variety × organ effect; and eijk = the residual error.
